<TITLE> Japan interested in Bangladeshi manpower: official </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 28 (bdnews24.com)  Japan is interested in importing Bangladeshi manpower to meet its increasing demand for workers. Koji Nojima, chairman of the Japan-Bangladesh Joint Committee for Commercial and Economic Cooperation, expressed the interest in meeting with foreign adviser Iftekhar Ahmed Chowdhury at the foreign ministry Wednesday. Nojima told the adviser that Japan had a negative population growth rate and that the population was ageing. He said the country needed a large number of workers for its economy, adding that the Indian and Vietnamese workers were already at work there. "Bangladesh is adopting a plan to enhance skills to provide labour to developed countries," Iftekhar told the media after the meeting. Japanese Ambassador to Bangladesh Masayuki Inoue was also present at the meeting. bdnews24
